-- Regulator suspends BES shares, awaits new information after plunge 
-- 
-- Fri Aug 01, 2014 11:24AM EDT
-- None



LISBON, Aug 1 (Reuters) - Portugal's CMVM securities market regulator suspended trading in shares of Banco Espirito Santo, pending new information to be released by the bank, after the stock plunged another 40 percent on Friday, adding to Thursday's 42 percent dive.

